> Falling into a stir-fry rut with the same veggie + sauce combo each week? We've got you covered. This version stars tender snow peas, bell pepper, and carrots, which are sautéed with ginger and garlic, then simmered in a tangy, savory-sweet blend of soy sauce, soy glaze, and rice wine vinegar until the sauce is thick and the veggies are glossy. Everything's tossed with slurpable, chewy ramen noodles, then topped with nutty sesame seeds. Dinner winner? We think so.

Bring a large #pot{} of @salt{}ed water to a boil. Wash and dry all produce.

Halve, core, and thinly slice @bell pepper{1} into strips. Trim, peel, and slice @carrot{3%oz} on a diagonal into ¼-inch-thick pieces. Trim and remove strings from half the @snow peas{8%oz} (use the rest as you like). Trim @scallions{2}; slice crosswise into 1-inch-thick pieces. Peel and mince @ginger{1%thumb} and @garlic{1%clove}.

> For 4 servings: Trim all the snow peas.

In a #small bowl{}, whisk together half the @cornstarch{1%tbsp} and ½ cup cold water until smooth. Whisk in @sweet soy glaze{4%tbsp}, @soy sauce{2%tbsp}, and half the @rice wine vinegar{5%tsp}. Set aside.

> For 4 servings: Use all the cornstarch, 1 cup water, and all the vinegar.

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tbsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add bell pepper, carrot, and a pinch of salt. Cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly softened, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Add trimmed snow peas and a pinch of salt. Cook, stirring, until veggies are tender, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add another drizzle of oil to pan, then stir in scallions, ginger, and garlic. Cook, stirring, for ~{30%seconds}. Transfer veggies to a #medium bowl{}.

> Add a splash of water if veggies begin to cook too quickly.

Pour sauce into pan used for veggies. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat. Simmer until thickened and glossy, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Once water is boiling, add @ramen noodles{6%oz} to pot. Cook for ~{2%minutes}, then drain and add to pan with sauce.

Return veggies to pan. Using #tongs{}, toss until everything is thoroughly coated in sauce.

Divide noodle stir-fry between shallow #bowls{} or plates. Sprinkle with as many @sesame seeds{1%tbsp} as you like and serve.